HEADWORD: Esophagotomy
<hw>E*soph`a*got"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>o'isofa`gos</grk> the esophagus + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to
cut.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of making an incision
into the esophagus, for the purpose of removing any foreign substance
that obstructs the passage.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>⟦oe⟧sophagotomy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

